# REPLACE_ME — rule title (human-readable)

## Agent init

**Mandatory:** Read this entire section before any other content in this file; execute every `Action:` line here immediately and retain every `Rule:` and `Knowledge:` line for the rest of this session.

- Rule: Every bullet in **Rules content** is exactly one line starting with `Knowledge:`, `Rule:`, or `Action:` — never wrap a rule across multiple lines.
- Rule: Type prefix is PascalCase with no spaces, first letter capitalized, followed by a colon and one space — Example: `Rule: Link constants.mdc instead of copying values.`
- Rule: `Knowledge:` bullets are context to retain; `Rule:` bullets are constraints to follow when this file applies; `Action:` bullets are steps to execute when their condition is met.
- Knowledge: REPLACE_ME — what this file is, in one sentence (scope, authority, audience).
- Knowledge: REPLACE_ME — when to load this file (tasks, paths, requests).
- Action: Read every `###` subsection in **Rules content** in order; store `Knowledge:` and `Rule:` bullets; execute `Action:` bullets when their condition applies.

